-- India's MCX says CEO resigned
-- By Himank Sharma and Zeba Siddiqui
-- Thu May 01, 2014 04:09AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 1 (Reuters) - Multi-Commodity Exchange of India Ltd (MCX) <MCEI.NS> on Thursday said Managing Director and Chief Executive Manoj Vaish has resigned after just three months in office citing health reasons.

Vaish, who took charge on Feb. 1, resigned from both posts and will work with the exchange's board to ensure a smooth transition to his successor, MCX said in a statement.